trimnul version 1.0.4
Release date: 2026-07-01
Description:
Fixed an uninitialized `Options` struct in main() that could cause the
default (non-dry-run) truncation behavior to silently no-op depending
on stack garbage. Implemented `-v`/`--verbose` (now the default) and
`-q`/`--quiet`, which previously had no effect. Replaced the unbounded
`alloca()` scan buffer with a checked heap allocation. Fixed a
`cursor_append` off-by-one that could silently drop the last byte of
an appended diagnostic string. Fixed a signed/unsigned mismatch in
`read_or_fail`'s short-read check. Fixed `open_flags_to_string`'s
`O_RDONLY` detection, which could never fire because `O_RDONLY` is 0.
Realigned the `trimnul` prototype/definition parameter indentation
left over from the earlier rename.

trimnul version 1.0.3
Release date: 2026-07-01
Description:
